The paper focuses on segmentation of surgical instruments in surgical videos, which is a computer vision task. Therefore, cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) is the most likely sub-category. The use of a U-shape network and attention module also suggests a focus on image segmentation, which is a sub-topic of cs.CV. 

The paper also mentions robot-assisted surgery, indicating a potential connection to robotics and automation, which falls under cs.RO (Robotics). Additionally, the use of transfer learning suggests a focus on machine learning, which could fall under cs.MM (Multimedia). 

The paper also discusses the use of a weighted loss function, which is a common technique in machine learning, suggesting a connection to cs.LG (Machine Learning). Finally, the paper proposes a novel network architecture, which could fall under cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence).
